<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CYLINDER
        SLEEVES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CYLINDER SLEEVES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the O-Rings with lubriplate and install one into each cylinder sleeve groove,
                    (without twist). Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050642">6.42</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Lightly lubriplate O-Ring area of sleeve and lower counterbore of crankcase to ease
                            installation and avoid O-Ring twist or pinch.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each cylinder sleeve uses two O-Rings.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, assure the proper shim(s) is installed, in the crankcase counterbore, so
                    cylinder sleeve protrusion is within specifications. Refer to "Cylinder Sleeve Fitting Procedure",
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_105.xml" xrefid="ef1050604">6.4</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050641" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2420" filename="../figeg2/eg2420.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.41.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Piston Crown</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Retaining Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Top Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Piston Pin</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Intermediate Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. Piston Skirt</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Oil Control Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. Connecting Rod</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050642" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3575" filename="../figeg3/eg3575.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.42.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Can</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Sleeve</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Crankcase</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Be sure the O-Rings are properly aligned in the groove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Lubriplate to the lower crankcase counterbore, then install the sleeve carefully.
                    If reusing sleeve, rotate 90&#176; from original position and install in the same bore from which it
                    was removed. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_123.xml" xrefid="ef1050643">6.43</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
